JwtAuthenticationEntryPoint
This class handles what exceptions need to be thrown when user is not authenticated The AuthenticationEntryPoint is an interface that provides the implementation for commence() method, which will be called whenever an exception is thrown, because the user is trying to access protected endpoint with INVALID CREDENTIALS, or without AUTHENTICATION.
